WEBVTT

00:00:39.018 --> 00:00:40.019
What is this place?

00:00:47.652 --> 00:00:48.486
What's wrong?

00:00:48.570 --> 00:00:49.988
Oh, it's just…

00:00:50.864 --> 00:00:51.990
How did we end up here?

00:00:52.574 --> 00:00:53.575
We are on a trip.

00:00:54.617 --> 00:00:55.451
What?

00:00:56.494 --> 00:00:57.537
You're doing it again.

00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:00.415
Want to nap some more?

00:01:46.711 --> 00:01:47.545
You're awake?

00:01:48.171 --> 00:01:49.005
Yes.

00:01:51.841 --> 00:01:53.676
Where did you go at this hour?

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:57.472
I went to the convenience store
to get some stuff for breakfast.

00:02:00.808 --> 00:02:02.644
You weren't here, so I was worried.

00:02:02.727 --> 00:02:04.437
Oh, you should get more sleep.

00:02:05.104 --> 00:02:07.190
I'm wide awake now. I'll go wash up.

00:02:25.208 --> 00:02:26.042
What's wrong?

00:02:27.043 --> 00:02:29.629
You seem a bit tired.
Did you not sleep well?

00:02:32.590 --> 00:02:34.342
I just had trouble dozing off.

00:02:36.511 --> 00:02:38.930
Get plenty of rest after work today.

00:02:39.597 --> 00:02:40.598
I'll do that.

00:02:42.934 --> 00:02:44.394
Drink some of this.

00:02:59.284 --> 00:03:00.451
What's wrong?

00:03:05.832 --> 00:03:06.666
You…

00:03:07.417 --> 00:03:09.002
-Who are you?
-Who are you?

00:03:10.336 --> 00:03:13.506
You hurt me in a lot of ways.
You don't even recognize me anymore?

00:03:32.567 --> 00:03:37.989
Ms. Seo Mi-rae, renew your subscription
to continue your date with Gu Yeong-il.

00:03:57.508 --> 00:03:59.093
Are you leaving already?

00:03:59.677 --> 00:04:02.930
Yes. I'm going to go home,
then go to work from there.

00:04:03.598 --> 00:04:05.683
-I'll see you later, then.
-Okay.

00:04:08.436 --> 00:04:09.604
GU YEONG-IL

00:04:09.687 --> 00:04:12.148
Why did you leave so fast?
You didn't even say goodbye.

00:04:12.231 --> 00:04:13.066
What is this?

00:04:16.319 --> 00:04:17.153
What's wrong?

00:04:19.697 --> 00:04:20.782
It's just…

00:04:22.033 --> 00:04:24.994
You seem a bit tired.
Did you not sleep well?

00:04:26.871 --> 00:04:29.123
I just had trouble dozing off.

00:04:31.167 --> 00:04:32.502
Last night,

00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:35.963
did something happen

00:04:37.131 --> 00:04:39.342
while I was asleep?

00:04:44.639 --> 00:04:49.560
You were just by yourself
because you couldn't fall asleep, right?

00:04:58.778 --> 00:04:59.987
I saw it.

00:05:02.323 --> 00:05:03.157
What…

00:05:03.991 --> 00:05:04.992
You saw what?

00:05:06.577 --> 00:05:07.870
Boyfriend on Demand.

00:05:12.375 --> 00:05:15.545
Well, what exactly did you see?

00:05:18.005 --> 00:05:19.340
I saw everything.

00:05:19.966 --> 00:05:20.967
That man too.

00:05:32.270 --> 00:05:33.271
Talk next time?

00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:37.984
This isn't… It's not what you think.

00:05:38.067 --> 00:05:41.737
So, things ended up this way somehow,
but please don't misunderstand.

00:05:42.738 --> 00:05:43.573
Misunderstand?

00:05:43.656 --> 00:05:46.159
You and Gu Yeong-il, I mean…

00:05:46.242 --> 00:05:49.245
That man has nothing to do with you.

00:05:51.038 --> 00:05:52.915
You know Mr. Min, right?

00:05:52.999 --> 00:05:56.002
He asked me for some reviews,

00:05:56.085 --> 00:06:01.257
so I ended up trying Boyfriend on Demand,
and things happened, and…

00:06:01.340 --> 00:06:04.552
I ended up making a character, and he…

00:06:04.635 --> 00:06:08.055
A character who looks just like me
was created by coincidence?

00:06:08.139 --> 00:06:13.895
I know this may all seem absurd.
I mean, I thought so too.

00:06:13.978 --> 00:06:16.564
But it really was a coincidence.

00:06:18.399 --> 00:06:20.776
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

00:06:22.028 --> 00:06:25.364
I just kept it from you
because it might sound weird.

00:06:29.660 --> 00:06:30.828
All right.

00:06:33.748 --> 00:06:34.790
Are you

00:06:35.708 --> 00:06:37.210
disappointed in me?

00:06:41.839 --> 00:06:43.132
To be honest,

00:06:44.509 --> 00:06:47.053
I'm not sure how I'm feeling right now.

00:06:53.267 --> 00:06:54.769
I guess I'll know after a while.

00:07:15.748 --> 00:07:19.919
I WANTED TO TELL YOU THAT I LIKE YOU

00:07:26.842 --> 00:07:27.760
PAYMENT COMPLETE

00:07:33.599 --> 00:07:35.142
-Hey, did you--
-Are you okay?

00:07:35.893 --> 00:07:36.894
What?

00:07:38.771 --> 00:07:40.106
Why did you leave like that?

00:07:48.864 --> 00:07:51.450
So you're telling me
he was the one who came to see me?

00:07:55.246 --> 00:07:57.081
So nothing happened for real?

00:07:58.040 --> 00:07:59.709
-No.
-And you didn't say anything?

00:08:01.544 --> 00:08:05.131
What is there to say about us?
You rejecting me was all there was to it.

00:08:12.888 --> 00:08:13.973
What was it like?

00:08:14.765 --> 00:08:15.683
What do you mean?

00:08:20.688 --> 00:08:22.189
When he saw you,

00:08:23.441 --> 00:08:24.859
what was his reaction?

00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:27.153
Well, he just

00:08:28.237 --> 00:08:29.572
acted like he'd seen a ghost.

00:08:32.158 --> 00:08:33.743
My good looks must've shocked him.

00:08:35.286 --> 00:08:36.454
What am I going to do?

00:08:38.205 --> 00:08:39.290
What did that man say?

00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:44.295
He doesn't know

00:08:45.212 --> 00:08:46.922
how he feels about this.

00:08:55.139 --> 00:08:56.223
Damn it.

00:08:59.268 --> 00:09:00.770
PRODUCER PARK KYEONG-NAM:
EARLIER…

00:09:00.853 --> 00:09:01.937
SO-YEONG

00:09:04.482 --> 00:09:06.525
Yes, So-yeong, let me get back to--

00:09:06.609 --> 00:09:07.902
Ms. Seo, this is bad!

00:09:07.985 --> 00:09:08.903
Huh?

00:09:19.121 --> 00:09:22.541
Director Hwang told Ms. Yun
that her contract was terminated.

00:09:31.175 --> 00:09:34.762
She needed someone to vent her anger on
and found the perfect target.

00:09:34.845 --> 00:09:35.763
Ms. Yun, how can I--

00:09:35.846 --> 00:09:37.098
-Move.
-Yes, ma'am.

00:09:39.975 --> 00:09:43.437
She said she had nothing more to lose
and stormed out.

00:09:43.521 --> 00:09:45.356
-Taxi! Hey!
-Please stop her.

00:09:51.362 --> 00:09:52.446
Oh, Yun Song…

00:09:52.530 --> 00:09:54.615
Wow, so this is what you've been up to.

00:09:54.699 --> 00:09:57.952
That coffee sure smells amazing,
doesn't it?

00:09:59.203 --> 00:10:01.122
Goodness, Hermès?

00:10:01.205 --> 00:10:03.708
-Wait, that's…
-When did you become so successful?

00:10:03.791 --> 00:10:06.377
I'm noticing a lot of things
I haven't seen before.

00:10:06.460 --> 00:10:09.255
I'm guessing you must've made a fortune
thanks to someone!

00:10:09.338 --> 00:10:12.174
Hey, you can't barge in here like this.
You startled me!

00:10:12.258 --> 00:10:13.592
-Mr. Hwang!
-Dear God!

00:10:13.676 --> 00:10:16.762
Do you think you're more startled
than someone who got axed?

00:10:16.846 --> 00:10:18.597
-Please just put that down.
-What?

00:10:18.681 --> 00:10:19.682
What?

00:10:23.436 --> 00:10:25.146
Shouldn't have shown off that mug.

00:10:26.188 --> 00:10:28.315
-Where is Ms. Yun?
-She's with Mr. Hwang.

00:10:28.399 --> 00:10:30.901
-I won't give it to you!
-Hey, have you lost your mind?

00:10:31.986 --> 00:10:34.029
-Let go!
-Wait!

00:10:34.113 --> 00:10:35.406
Watch the finger!

00:10:35.906 --> 00:10:37.074
Let go!

00:10:38.909 --> 00:10:40.494
God, my wrist!

00:10:41.078 --> 00:10:42.288
It wasn't that bad.

00:10:45.249 --> 00:10:47.710
You handle that crap with such care,

00:10:47.793 --> 00:10:51.797
but don't care that all that drawing
left me barely able to hold chopsticks.

00:10:51.881 --> 00:10:54.049
Are authors less important to you
than a mug?

00:10:54.550 --> 00:10:55.718
Huh?

00:10:55.801 --> 00:10:58.012
I'll have you know
this is a workplace injury.

00:10:58.095 --> 00:11:00.848
Do you have any idea
how much this wrist is worth?

00:11:05.978 --> 00:11:07.188
Ms. Yun.

00:11:10.775 --> 00:11:15.070
Seo? Where have you been all this time?

00:11:15.571 --> 00:11:17.823
Please calm down. We can talk--

00:11:17.907 --> 00:11:20.868
I can't put up with this crap anymore.

00:11:25.748 --> 00:11:26.999
Let's go.

00:11:27.082 --> 00:11:30.169
No need to stick around
with this shitty company any longer.

00:11:35.382 --> 00:11:36.425
But…

00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:41.806
-You can't just leave like this.
-Let go.

00:11:41.889 --> 00:11:43.974
Let's try to convince the director--

00:11:44.058 --> 00:11:44.892
Let go!

00:11:44.975 --> 00:11:45.935
Ms. Yun, please!

00:12:19.051 --> 00:12:23.138
Goodness, that temper of hers.
She really needs to get it under control.

00:12:29.144 --> 00:12:31.981
Why are you looking at me?
What's with the grim faces?

00:12:39.947 --> 00:12:43.534
EPISODE 10
AN UTTERLY NORMAL FUTURE

00:12:58.966 --> 00:13:00.634
I got scratched a little.

00:13:25.910 --> 00:13:26.744
There.

00:13:28.454 --> 00:13:29.496
Thank you.

00:13:30.748 --> 00:13:32.833
Shouldn't you be checking in on Ms. Yun?

00:13:34.084 --> 00:13:35.920
Once she calms down a bit.

00:13:42.092 --> 00:13:45.971
About what we were talking about
this morning…

00:13:46.472 --> 00:13:47.973
You already explained everything.

00:13:51.018 --> 00:13:52.269
Are you okay?

00:13:56.065 --> 00:13:59.360
Did you see how she pulled
a shoulder throw on Mr. Hwang?

00:13:59.944 --> 00:14:01.362
Stop making it a big deal.

00:14:01.946 --> 00:14:02.780
What did I do?

00:14:04.740 --> 00:14:07.493
What's wrong? Are you hurt? Let me see.

00:14:07.576 --> 00:14:08.744
It's nothing.

00:14:09.328 --> 00:14:11.497
Look at her face. This won't do.

00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:13.999
Let's head out.
What you need is a bowl of unadon.

00:14:14.583 --> 00:14:16.168
You're having lunch, aren't you?

00:14:18.504 --> 00:14:21.423
I have a meeting with an author later.

00:14:22.257 --> 00:14:24.426
Yeah? That's too bad.

00:14:25.260 --> 00:14:28.097
Are you treating your teammates
to unadon, then?

00:14:28.180 --> 00:14:29.515
Doors opening.

00:14:42.653 --> 00:14:43.487
What is it?

00:14:45.572 --> 00:14:48.075
I thought we got interrupted earlier.

00:14:50.077 --> 00:14:52.162
Are you sure you're okay?

00:14:54.415 --> 00:14:55.332
Yes.

00:15:07.177 --> 00:15:09.013
Look at me.

00:15:19.773 --> 00:15:21.191
You actually made it?

00:15:28.407 --> 00:15:29.783
Doors opening.

00:15:32.995 --> 00:15:34.580
Well, Hwany

00:15:36.248 --> 00:15:37.833
is waiting for me.

00:15:38.834 --> 00:15:39.793
I'll be going now.

00:15:42.171 --> 00:15:43.756
Okay. Bye.

00:15:45.049 --> 00:15:45.883
Right.

00:15:55.642 --> 00:15:57.311
I had a strange feeling.

00:15:58.645 --> 00:16:03.776
That Park Kyeong-nam had gone back
to the man I once knew him as.

00:16:05.486 --> 00:16:06.570
This unease.

00:16:07.571 --> 00:16:09.406
Why does it feel so familiar?

00:16:32.096 --> 00:16:34.765
What I need to do
is pretend everything's okay.

00:16:37.142 --> 00:16:38.268
PRODUCER PARK KYEONG-NAM

00:16:38.352 --> 00:16:39.770
Good luck with your meeting.

00:16:53.659 --> 00:16:57.871
GOOD LUCK WITH YOUR MEETING!
(UNREAD)

00:17:02.376 --> 00:17:03.460
Are you busy?

00:17:05.129 --> 00:17:06.296
You like him that much?

00:17:08.882 --> 00:17:12.678
When you like someone,
you go all in, no matter what happens.

00:17:13.220 --> 00:17:14.138
That's a no-no.

00:17:15.347 --> 00:17:16.431
How come?

00:17:16.515 --> 00:17:18.851
It's just how relationship dynamics work.

00:17:18.934 --> 00:17:23.063
Whoever shows their affection more
ends up getting dragged around in the end.

00:17:23.147 --> 00:17:24.898
You're being dramatic.

00:17:24.982 --> 00:17:27.818
Think about your past relationships.

00:17:30.237 --> 00:17:33.824
Fine, let's say you're right.
What's wrong with getting dragged around?

00:17:36.160 --> 00:17:36.994
I mean,

00:17:37.077 --> 00:17:40.455
if you're cool with staring into
your phone all day, waiting for a reply,

00:17:40.539 --> 00:17:43.834
and going, "Has he lost interest in me?
Is this a one-sided thing?"

00:17:44.710 --> 00:17:47.296
while trembling with anxiety,
then it's okay.

00:17:49.631 --> 00:17:51.550
Just put a curse on me, will you?

00:17:51.633 --> 00:17:54.219
And that's how the vicious cycle goes on.

00:17:54.845 --> 00:17:58.432
You get anxious. You get clingy.
He grows distant day by day.

00:17:58.932 --> 00:18:00.767
This especially applies to you.

00:18:00.851 --> 00:18:03.270
When things get a little awkward
for the first time,

00:18:03.353 --> 00:18:06.607
you need to be extra careful.

00:18:08.817 --> 00:18:09.818
Why?

00:18:10.319 --> 00:18:15.240
That's when it starts to show
which one of you likes the other way more.

00:18:16.158 --> 00:18:21.038
That's when the lord and the serf
in the relationship are determined.

00:18:22.122 --> 00:18:23.624
Always so dramatic.

00:18:23.707 --> 00:18:24.833
ARE YOU BUSY?

00:18:33.550 --> 00:18:34.718
You've been moody lately.

00:18:35.719 --> 00:18:38.639
The other day, you were grinning.
Today, you look like crap.

00:18:38.722 --> 00:18:41.099
What are you talking about?
I'm just eating my food.

00:18:43.060 --> 00:18:44.186
Are you busy?

00:18:46.647 --> 00:18:47.981
I'm out to eat right--

00:18:48.065 --> 00:18:49.524
You're seeing someone, huh?

00:18:51.652 --> 00:18:54.071
Want me to guess who? It's too easy.

00:18:54.821 --> 00:18:56.531
I can act like I don't know if you want.

00:18:57.574 --> 00:18:58.492
What?

00:18:59.534 --> 00:19:00.410
You knew?

00:19:01.078 --> 00:19:04.581
Man, don't treat me like an NPC.
How could I not know?

00:19:05.165 --> 00:19:08.835
I had my suspicions the moment I heard
you were working late every Friday.

00:19:08.919 --> 00:19:10.837
You can talk to me about Ms. Seo.

00:19:10.921 --> 00:19:13.257
Forget it. I can't talk to you about her.

00:19:13.340 --> 00:19:15.884
What's it about?
So there is something going on.

00:19:22.599 --> 00:19:23.433
Well…

00:19:26.395 --> 00:19:27.646
It's just that…

00:19:27.729 --> 00:19:30.482
What? Did she do something to upset you?

00:19:31.275 --> 00:19:34.319
No, I wouldn't say that, but…

00:19:34.403 --> 00:19:35.237
Are you mad?

00:19:35.988 --> 00:19:38.657
-Are you fuming?
-No, it's not that bad.

00:19:38.740 --> 00:19:40.284
What then, are you just sulking?

00:19:41.451 --> 00:19:42.286
Huh?

00:19:42.369 --> 00:19:46.290
I mean, if you're not upset or mad at her,
then you're just sulking.

00:19:47.958 --> 00:19:48.792
I'm…

00:19:49.459 --> 00:19:51.336
I'm sulking? Me?

00:19:51.420 --> 00:19:55.424
Hey, it's nothing to be embarrassed about.
We all get sulky.

00:19:57.009 --> 00:19:58.760
No, I've never sulked before.

00:19:58.844 --> 00:19:59.803
Is that right?

00:20:00.304 --> 00:20:02.556
Sure. Of course you haven't.

00:20:05.309 --> 00:20:06.143
Hey.

00:20:10.856 --> 00:20:11.940
So…

00:20:13.984 --> 00:20:16.820
why do people normally get sulky
with someone?

00:20:30.250 --> 00:20:32.169
ARE YOU BUSY?
(READ)

00:20:32.252 --> 00:20:33.837
He left me on read?

00:20:36.298 --> 00:20:38.300
PRODUCER PARK KYEONG-NAM
CALL

00:20:39.259 --> 00:20:42.804
Don't get clingy! Don't call him
just because you're a bit worried!

00:20:42.888 --> 00:20:44.973
That's a fast track to a rut, you know.

00:21:00.364 --> 00:21:01.948
I'm going to bed now.

00:21:04.409 --> 00:21:05.911
What are you so worried about?

00:21:08.914 --> 00:21:10.874
It's not like you committed a crime.

00:21:14.503 --> 00:21:17.422
As long as nothing happened
between you two, that's fine.

00:21:19.466 --> 00:21:20.759
Wait.

00:21:21.343 --> 00:21:24.596
If that man ever acts petty, tell me.

00:21:26.473 --> 00:21:27.307
What?

00:21:28.683 --> 00:21:31.937
Let me know if he frustrates you
or gives you a hard time.

00:21:33.647 --> 00:21:34.481
Why?

00:21:35.482 --> 00:21:36.733
I'll help you.

00:21:48.078 --> 00:21:48.912
Is everything okay?

00:21:48.995 --> 00:21:49.830
GU YEONG-IL

00:21:52.249 --> 00:21:54.084
Okay. Good night.

00:22:16.398 --> 00:22:18.442
OKAY GOOD NIGHT
(READ)

00:22:20.193 --> 00:22:22.529
Why do people normally get sulky
with someone?

00:22:22.612 --> 00:22:23.864
Because they like them.

00:22:26.575 --> 00:22:30.162
Wow. You must really like Ms. Seo.

00:22:41.381 --> 00:22:43.633
-Did you have break--
-Did you get some sleep?

00:22:45.260 --> 00:22:46.761
I had breakfast.

00:22:47.846 --> 00:22:49.347
I got some sleep.

00:23:05.197 --> 00:23:06.198
What's going on?

00:23:06.823 --> 00:23:08.658
He's acting somewhat cold.

00:23:14.623 --> 00:23:16.583
Why is she avoiding my eyes?

00:23:20.045 --> 00:23:20.962
I'll…

00:23:23.006 --> 00:23:24.424
get going now.

00:23:25.217 --> 00:23:26.343
Okay.

00:23:45.403 --> 00:23:46.571
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND

00:23:47.656 --> 00:23:49.950
-Isn't that Yun Song?
-Yeah, that's her.

00:23:52.327 --> 00:23:54.120
Are you here for the Karrot trade?

00:23:54.204 --> 00:23:55.413
Oh, yes, Karrot.

00:24:00.085 --> 00:24:01.253
Did you format this?

00:24:01.336 --> 00:24:02.379
No.

00:24:02.462 --> 00:24:03.755
Can you do it right now?

00:24:08.885 --> 00:24:12.305
You've got such a kind heart, Song.

00:24:14.349 --> 00:24:16.226
I should help you get motivated.

00:24:22.816 --> 00:24:25.235
If it's too much trouble,
I can do it later.

00:24:25.318 --> 00:24:27.737
I'll wire you the money.
What's your account…

00:24:33.201 --> 00:24:34.786
Hello?

00:24:36.913 --> 00:24:38.748
What the heck? Are you not selling it?

00:24:45.839 --> 00:24:46.798
I'm sorry.

00:24:55.390 --> 00:24:57.475
This is driving me crazy.

00:25:08.153 --> 00:25:10.196
-Hey.
-What are you up to now?

00:25:10.280 --> 00:25:12.449
You said
you've lost your appetite recently,

00:25:12.532 --> 00:25:14.075
so I'm going to make you soup.

00:25:16.369 --> 00:25:17.996
Are you trying to drive me crazy?

00:25:18.079 --> 00:25:20.624
Why carrot soup, of all things?

00:25:21.291 --> 00:25:22.792
What's wrong? It's what you like.

00:25:22.876 --> 00:25:25.086
You almost got karroted off.
You know that?

00:25:25.712 --> 00:25:27.130
Did I do something wrong?

00:25:27.213 --> 00:25:28.882
Yes, you did!

00:25:28.965 --> 00:25:32.761
I didn't have to know any of this,
but you made me find out.

00:25:32.844 --> 00:25:35.305
You're the reason I ended up like this.

00:25:35.889 --> 00:25:39.893
Hey, stop lashing out at me
and tell me what this is about.

00:25:41.353 --> 00:25:42.354
I don't know.

00:25:43.355 --> 00:25:46.733
Everyone keeps mocking me for liking you.

00:25:49.235 --> 00:25:50.070
Mocking you?

00:25:51.780 --> 00:25:52.614
Who is?

00:25:53.490 --> 00:25:56.660
They are saying
things won't work out between us.

00:25:57.911 --> 00:25:59.287
Who said that?

00:26:00.288 --> 00:26:04.000
Everyone except you and me. All of them!

00:26:05.585 --> 00:26:06.419
Come here.

00:26:10.173 --> 00:26:11.007
It's okay.

00:26:11.841 --> 00:26:12.676
It's okay.

00:26:15.762 --> 00:26:16.680
Here.

00:26:19.557 --> 00:26:20.892
-You like?
-Yeah.

00:26:22.644 --> 00:26:24.229
Why do you like me?

00:26:24.813 --> 00:26:27.899
You only like me
because you have to, don't you?

00:26:30.568 --> 00:26:31.820
Why do you like me?

00:26:32.987 --> 00:26:34.155
You're good-looking.

00:26:34.781 --> 00:26:37.450
You're a good cook. You're nice to me.

00:26:37.534 --> 00:26:40.328
You're cute, and you're kind.

00:26:42.122 --> 00:26:46.960
-Then why are you being like this to me?
-You might have a hundred good qualities.

00:26:47.460 --> 00:26:50.046
But you have one fatal flaw.

00:26:50.130 --> 00:26:52.132
I didn't ask about my pros and cons.

00:26:52.841 --> 00:26:55.593
I asked why you're being like this to me.
Do you hate me now?

00:26:57.512 --> 00:26:59.139
Then what's the issue?

00:27:01.391 --> 00:27:05.228
I asked you first. Answer me.
Tell me why you like me.

00:27:10.316 --> 00:27:11.151
I just

00:27:12.861 --> 00:27:14.571
like it when you're happy.

00:27:15.739 --> 00:27:17.240
There's no other reason.

00:27:17.991 --> 00:27:21.578
That's not what I'm asking.
What do you like about me?

00:27:21.661 --> 00:27:22.912
Why do you like me?

00:27:22.996 --> 00:27:24.748
Liking you

00:27:25.999 --> 00:27:27.834
and liking you being happy,

00:27:28.752 --> 00:27:29.836
are they different?

00:27:30.503 --> 00:27:33.423
I'd be okay with it
even if you had 10,000 flaws.

00:27:34.174 --> 00:27:35.258
But

00:27:35.341 --> 00:27:39.304
if you absolutely can't stand my one flaw…

00:27:41.848 --> 00:27:42.974
then you can leave.

00:27:45.185 --> 00:27:46.186
Because

00:27:46.895 --> 00:27:49.230
your happiness is what matters to me most.

00:28:05.163 --> 00:28:06.498
Did I give you such a hard time?

00:28:08.458 --> 00:28:11.795
It's not because of you.
It's because of me.

00:28:12.295 --> 00:28:16.216
Who cares how others think about me
when I like you so much?

00:28:16.716 --> 00:28:19.803
I'll stop going on Karrot.
I'm done with that now.

00:28:21.054 --> 00:28:23.097
What's this Karrot you keep mentioning?

00:28:24.974 --> 00:28:26.142
You don't need to know.

00:28:27.936 --> 00:28:29.354
Eat the soup first.

00:28:29.437 --> 00:28:32.440
It's going to get cold. You seemed hungry.

00:28:33.650 --> 00:28:35.068
-Is it good?
-Yes.

00:28:35.151 --> 00:28:36.319
It's good, huh?

00:28:37.111 --> 00:28:38.655
-Yum yum.
-Yum yum, nom nom.

00:28:38.738 --> 00:28:40.448
Yum yum, nom nom. Here.

00:28:44.410 --> 00:28:45.578
There.

00:28:46.496 --> 00:28:47.914
I put away all my mugs.

00:28:48.498 --> 00:28:50.083
She might barge in again any day.

00:28:50.625 --> 00:28:54.295
We can't let our guard down
until Yun Song has calmed down.

00:28:54.379 --> 00:28:58.424
Sir, how could you do that
without even giving me a heads-up?

00:28:58.508 --> 00:29:02.679
Hey, I only did that to save you
from the trouble of telling her yourself.

00:29:02.762 --> 00:29:04.013
God, I'm hurt.

00:29:04.097 --> 00:29:08.101
Even Mr. Min said he didn't want
to make an issue out of the plagiarism,

00:29:08.184 --> 00:29:10.103
and the rest is just a private matter.

00:29:10.186 --> 00:29:11.938
Did she commit a sin or something?

00:29:12.021 --> 00:29:15.525
Until the public unrest dies down,
put her work on hold,

00:29:16.025 --> 00:29:18.444
and focus on managing the other authors.

00:29:18.528 --> 00:29:20.864
Putting her on hiatus would be inevitable,

00:29:21.865 --> 00:29:24.117
but I don't agree
with terminating her contract.

00:29:24.200 --> 00:29:25.118
Oh, that's right.

00:29:26.119 --> 00:29:29.038
You're my boss.
Oh my, it totally slipped my mind!

00:29:29.122 --> 00:29:30.164
Mr. Hwang!

00:29:38.756 --> 00:29:40.341
Fine, then.

00:29:40.425 --> 00:29:43.511
I'll reconsider it.
Put her on hiatus for now.

00:29:44.554 --> 00:29:46.222
But I can't promise you anything.

00:29:46.723 --> 00:29:50.268
Now please leave, ma'am.
You're making me very uncomfortable.

00:30:09.913 --> 00:30:10.747
Going somewhere?

00:30:12.206 --> 00:30:14.125
I need some air.
I'm going to work outside.

00:30:32.977 --> 00:30:34.729
Why are you here by yourself?

00:30:36.439 --> 00:30:38.358
Oh, everyone else went home.

00:30:39.025 --> 00:30:39.943
They all went home?

00:30:40.026 --> 00:30:44.364
Yun Song's series has been put on hold,
so Mi-rae's back to leaving work on time.

00:30:45.031 --> 00:30:47.700
Only the team leader remains
to hold down the fort.

00:30:48.701 --> 00:30:50.119
The nerve of those punks.

00:30:50.203 --> 00:30:52.830
They've never once told me
they were leaving before…

00:30:57.377 --> 00:30:58.252
You too?

00:31:03.675 --> 00:31:05.176
Huh? You didn't go home?

00:31:05.259 --> 00:31:07.428
No. I was working outside.

00:31:08.262 --> 00:31:10.765
Wait, everyone went home?
Are you here by yourself?

00:31:10.848 --> 00:31:13.017
Mm-hmm. They all left a while ago.

00:31:13.977 --> 00:31:18.231
I haven't said anything to you guys,
but I have a lot pent up inside.

00:31:18.314 --> 00:31:22.235
I never talk about it,
but now that you're here, Mi-rae…

00:31:36.833 --> 00:31:40.837
For the first time since we got together,
he left work without even telling me.

00:31:41.504 --> 00:31:42.839
What does this mean?

00:31:46.634 --> 00:31:47.969
-I'M OFF TO A MEETING.
-OKAY.

00:31:48.052 --> 00:31:49.637
HEADING BACK NOW
WANT SOME COOKIES?

00:31:49.721 --> 00:31:50.555
I'M GOOD

00:31:50.638 --> 00:31:52.974
-WHEN DOES YOUR MEETING END?
-IT JUST ENDED

00:31:53.057 --> 00:31:54.976
-THAT WAS LONG, YOU SHOULD EAT LUNCH
-OKAY

00:32:06.946 --> 00:32:08.781
She left work without even telling me?

00:32:14.287 --> 00:32:15.455
He's changed.

00:32:16.205 --> 00:32:19.959
Ever since he found out about
Boyfriend on Demand, he's changed.

00:32:35.391 --> 00:32:37.351
She left first and didn't even text me.

00:32:47.236 --> 00:32:49.322
WOULD YOU LIKE TO CANCEL
YOUR SUBSCRIPTION?

00:32:49.906 --> 00:32:52.408
I'll help you patch things up
with that guy.

00:33:12.595 --> 00:33:13.429
Back so soon?

00:33:16.724 --> 00:33:17.558
Want a drink?

00:33:23.439 --> 00:33:24.524
What's the problem?

00:33:26.067 --> 00:33:28.027
Tell me what's troubling you the most.

00:33:29.654 --> 00:33:30.655
I just

00:33:31.864 --> 00:33:33.950
don't know what he's thinking.

00:33:34.909 --> 00:33:37.912
Besides, I keep obsessing over
every little thing about him.

00:33:38.496 --> 00:33:41.332
I'm glued to my phone all the time,
wondering when he'll reply.

00:33:41.999 --> 00:33:44.043
It feels as though
my life has disappeared.

00:33:44.794 --> 00:33:46.212
Why not just ask what he's thinking?

00:33:48.339 --> 00:33:50.842
I can't bring myself to do that.

00:33:51.926 --> 00:33:53.845
And you don't want to break up like this?

00:33:59.559 --> 00:34:04.313
So, you feel that he has changed
after he found me, but you can't ask him.

00:34:05.273 --> 00:34:08.192
At the same time, doing nothing
makes you nervous and frustrated.

00:34:08.776 --> 00:34:09.610
Is that it?

00:34:11.404 --> 00:34:12.321
Yes.

00:34:12.905 --> 00:34:15.408
Then we'll have to find out
how he feels about you.

00:34:17.368 --> 00:34:18.244
But how?

00:34:25.001 --> 00:34:26.460
Let's go somewhere else.

00:34:39.640 --> 00:34:40.683
Seo Mi-rae.

00:35:02.496 --> 00:35:03.331
What is this?

00:35:04.290 --> 00:35:05.124
Are you surprised?

00:35:06.292 --> 00:35:09.629
Why are we at a place like this?
And what's with that outfit?

00:35:14.091 --> 00:35:15.801
Did I make your heart flutter?

00:35:20.973 --> 00:35:24.060
I won't get the wrong idea.
I know full well that you like that man.

00:35:26.354 --> 00:35:29.523
Isn't it confusing when the familiar
gets mixed up with the unfamiliar?

00:35:30.524 --> 00:35:35.446
In an unexpected situation like this,
people tend to reveal their true feelings.

00:35:35.529 --> 00:35:36.864
The heart cannot lie.

00:35:38.741 --> 00:35:40.660
Can you make it make sense?

00:35:42.828 --> 00:35:46.582
Well, I'm proposing that we create
a situation that he won't expect.

00:35:48.501 --> 00:35:52.338
Then, we'll be able to confirm
whether his heart still beats for you.

00:35:57.760 --> 00:36:01.180
Show up at a familiar location,
but in a getup that he's unfamiliar with.

00:36:06.978 --> 00:36:08.271
Hello.

00:36:09.188 --> 00:36:10.439
-You look so pretty!
-Hi.

00:36:11.649 --> 00:36:12.733
-Hello.
-What?

00:36:13.484 --> 00:36:14.944
-She's wearing a skirt!
-What?

00:36:15.027 --> 00:36:16.654
You look so pretty today.

00:36:17.238 --> 00:36:18.114
Really!

00:36:21.993 --> 00:36:23.244
Ms. Seo!

00:36:23.327 --> 00:36:24.578
Good morning.

00:36:24.662 --> 00:36:26.205
What's this?

00:36:26.289 --> 00:36:28.457
What's going on?
Are you also being interviewed?

00:36:29.333 --> 00:36:30.167
Interviewed?

00:36:32.003 --> 00:36:34.088
I hope the trip here
wasn't too inconvenient.

00:36:34.171 --> 00:36:36.424
I hope our article
didn't inconvenience you.

00:36:36.507 --> 00:36:38.426
Oh well, I don't mind such things.

00:36:38.509 --> 00:36:40.636
Webtoons Monthly is here for an interview.

00:36:41.846 --> 00:36:45.016
All the recent articles are about Ms. Yun,

00:36:45.516 --> 00:36:49.353
but the contest awards ceremony
and the new releases are coming up.

00:36:49.937 --> 00:36:51.439
He's on a full charm offensive.

00:36:51.522 --> 00:36:52.940
Please take good care of us.

00:36:53.024 --> 00:36:54.692
Why isn't he here yet?

00:36:55.359 --> 00:36:56.193
Who?

00:36:57.278 --> 00:36:58.863
They're here for Mr. Hwang and--

00:36:58.946 --> 00:37:00.197
Hey, Kyeong-nam!

00:37:05.911 --> 00:37:06.912
No way.

00:37:12.793 --> 00:37:13.627
Holy crap.

00:37:22.219 --> 00:37:23.387
Hello.

00:37:24.263 --> 00:37:26.182
Hey! Can you hurry up, please?

00:37:26.265 --> 00:37:28.768
-Yes, sir.
-They're waiting for you, Mr. Park.

00:37:31.187 --> 00:37:32.188
Are you okay?

00:37:32.938 --> 00:37:34.607
Yeah, I'm fine.

00:37:37.109 --> 00:37:39.195
Why did she have to look so pretty today?

00:37:39.945 --> 00:37:41.113
So much for confirming!

00:37:41.197 --> 00:37:43.908
It only confirmed
that my heart's still alive and well.

00:37:44.700 --> 00:37:48.120
Man, he's good.
I wasn't expecting a countermove.

00:37:49.288 --> 00:37:51.457
I spent all that money at the salon
for nothing.

00:37:52.249 --> 00:37:53.834
This won't do. Change of plans.

00:37:54.710 --> 00:37:58.047
Before we confirm his heart,
let's manage yours first.

00:38:01.926 --> 00:38:03.052
Leave your heart here.

00:38:05.429 --> 00:38:08.015
Like the Tin Man
who was missing his heart.

00:38:08.099 --> 00:38:10.851
Step into the mindset
of someone living without a heart.

00:38:12.144 --> 00:38:14.980
I'm sure you'll feel a lot more relaxed
once you have no heart.

00:39:00.693 --> 00:39:01.944
Stay put at home.

00:39:17.001 --> 00:39:19.753
My heart isn't here.

00:39:19.837 --> 00:39:22.339
-A bug! On your back!
-What? Me?

00:39:22.423 --> 00:39:25.009
Oh God, get it off! Get it off me, please!

00:39:25.593 --> 00:39:27.011
That's why today…

00:39:27.511 --> 00:39:28.762
Please!

00:39:31.390 --> 00:39:33.893
What was it? Goodness, that's creepy.

00:39:34.602 --> 00:39:35.436
It's nothing.

00:39:38.647 --> 00:39:41.650
…I won't lose my cool,
no matter what happens.

00:39:46.572 --> 00:39:48.949
She grabbed a bug with her bare hands?

00:39:58.918 --> 00:40:01.003
I'm sorry. The meeting ended a bit late.

00:40:01.086 --> 00:40:02.004
Oh, it's fine.

00:40:02.087 --> 00:40:03.339
Sorry about that.

00:40:09.720 --> 00:40:11.680
CUSTOM-TAILORED BOYFRIEND GU YEONG-IL

00:40:14.433 --> 00:40:15.267
Mr. Min,

00:40:16.018 --> 00:40:17.853
what is that?

00:40:18.562 --> 00:40:20.981
-Excuse me?
-Oh, I meant Gu Yeong-il.

00:40:22.066 --> 00:40:23.275
Oh, this?

00:40:23.359 --> 00:40:27.029
It was developed as a special bonus
for the users who didn't like our themes

00:40:27.112 --> 00:40:28.781
because they were too contrived,

00:40:28.864 --> 00:40:31.951
but it's gotten so popular
that we have a dedicated team for it now.

00:40:32.993 --> 00:40:35.496
If it's custom-tailored,
does it cover everything?

00:40:36.080 --> 00:40:39.208
We try to make it as close
to the user's ideal man as possible.

00:40:39.291 --> 00:40:40.960
Personality, looks, everything.

00:40:41.544 --> 00:40:44.755
Whoa, then he must be a perfect man.

00:40:44.838 --> 00:40:49.301
Some say that he's definitely
a cut above a human boyfriend.

00:40:49.385 --> 00:40:52.054
But as it turns out,
that wasn't the case for some.

00:40:54.431 --> 00:40:55.432
Why not?

00:40:56.517 --> 00:40:59.937
Aren't movies more fun
when you don't know the ending?

00:41:00.521 --> 00:41:05.150
The man of your dreams has appeared,
but you already know he will like you,

00:41:05.234 --> 00:41:08.070
and that breaks the immersion
for some people.

00:41:09.321 --> 00:41:12.241
Besides, love is about
giving your heart to someone

00:41:12.324 --> 00:41:14.827
when you have no idea what will come next.

00:41:15.995 --> 00:41:19.164
And it's not like
love can simply be mimicked.

00:41:19.665 --> 00:41:20.791
That's the hardest part.

00:41:23.294 --> 00:41:24.295
True that!

00:41:26.297 --> 00:41:29.341
With TMTK gone, it feels like a free win,
and I don't love that.

00:41:31.051 --> 00:41:33.554
But has it really been canceled?
It hasn't, right?

00:41:33.637 --> 00:41:35.222
I don't know much about it.

00:41:35.973 --> 00:41:39.810
Setting the second male lead aside,
there's still so much left to wrap up.

00:41:39.893 --> 00:41:42.605
There's the aunt's embezzlement
during the Cebu construction

00:41:42.688 --> 00:41:45.482
and the affair between the chairman
and Director Song.

00:41:45.983 --> 00:41:48.068
When does she plan on revealing all that?

00:41:48.152 --> 00:41:51.071
Try talking to Ms. Yun.
You're a fan, so she might tell you.

00:41:51.155 --> 00:41:52.281
A fan?

00:41:52.823 --> 00:41:53.741
Are you insane?

00:41:53.824 --> 00:41:57.870
I only read it to review the coloring work
So-yeong poured her heart and soul into.

00:42:00.914 --> 00:42:04.251
About that thing earlier on…
Gu Yeong-il, was it?

00:42:05.419 --> 00:42:07.504
Do you think So-yeong might have made one?

00:42:07.588 --> 00:42:11.300
I'm a little curious as to
what her Gu Yeong-il would look like.

00:42:13.135 --> 00:42:13.969
Well…

00:42:15.679 --> 00:42:18.432
how do you think you'd feel
if he looked like you?

00:42:18.515 --> 00:42:19.600
Me?

00:42:24.855 --> 00:42:26.523
Come on, man!

00:42:26.607 --> 00:42:29.777
I'd love it, of course!
That would mean I'm the man of her dreams.

00:42:31.236 --> 00:42:32.404
Hold on a second.

00:42:32.905 --> 00:42:37.576
He would only look like me
and be better than me in every other way.

00:42:37.660 --> 00:42:38.911
Should I be worried?

00:42:39.870 --> 00:42:43.040
Nah, I shouldn't be. I can beat him.

00:42:46.293 --> 00:42:50.506
Because I like her more. That jerk
would only be pretending to like her.

00:42:51.757 --> 00:42:55.219
How would that jerk know
how pretty and adorable So-yeong is?

00:42:56.261 --> 00:42:58.931
Damn, talking about her
makes me miss her more.

00:43:07.481 --> 00:43:09.566
-Hwany, I'm sorry.
-Huh?

00:43:51.150 --> 00:43:52.651
I thought you left for the day.

00:43:54.194 --> 00:43:57.030
Mi-rae just went to get us some snacks.
You're missing out.

00:43:57.114 --> 00:43:58.699
Where did she go?

00:43:59.908 --> 00:44:01.201
The café right out front.

00:44:44.578 --> 00:44:45.913
Huh? What?

00:44:46.538 --> 00:44:47.623
Why…

00:44:47.706 --> 00:44:49.082
Did you run all the way here?

00:44:50.959 --> 00:44:51.794
I just

00:44:52.753 --> 00:44:54.254
wanted to follow my heart.

00:44:55.130 --> 00:44:56.215
What?

00:44:57.216 --> 00:44:58.884
To see you when I want to see you…

00:45:00.928 --> 00:45:02.679
and hug you when I want to hug you.

00:45:11.730 --> 00:45:12.815
Should I not do that?

00:45:14.775 --> 00:45:15.692
Well…

00:45:39.508 --> 00:45:40.342
Do it.

00:45:41.844 --> 00:45:44.513
That's what I want to do too.

00:46:17.337 --> 00:46:18.505
Are you sure about this?

00:46:18.589 --> 00:46:22.384
There's no better person
to help us strengthen our scenarios.

00:46:22.467 --> 00:46:24.136
I don't know about this.

00:46:24.219 --> 00:46:28.056
She probably stays at home all day
watching dating shows and playing games.

00:46:29.641 --> 00:46:32.352
I doubt she'll be capable of
communicating with us.

00:46:59.504 --> 00:47:01.006
Boyfriend on Demand?

00:47:02.466 --> 00:47:03.300
Yes.

00:47:04.134 --> 00:47:06.053
I am Boyfriend on Demand.

00:47:07.638 --> 00:47:10.057
This is a special case for us, too,

00:47:10.641 --> 00:47:14.311
but we were really impressed
by your analysis of our themes.

00:47:14.394 --> 00:47:15.896
That's why we reached out.

00:47:16.939 --> 00:47:17.940
Ji-yeon,

00:47:19.274 --> 00:47:20.525
what is your dream?

00:47:20.609 --> 00:47:25.072
I'd like to review all 900 boyfriends,
then publish a book about that, and so on.

00:47:26.365 --> 00:47:28.283
You plan on meeting all 900 of them?

00:47:28.367 --> 00:47:30.369
Yes. I'm almost there.

00:47:30.953 --> 00:47:32.371
Then you won't live your life?

00:47:34.414 --> 00:47:35.874
What I mean to say is…

00:47:38.418 --> 00:47:40.253
I'm living my life to the fullest.

00:47:40.337 --> 00:47:44.299
You must have thought Boyfriend on Demand
is all I do. Not at all.

00:47:44.383 --> 00:47:47.469
Then do you have other hobbies?

00:47:48.053 --> 00:47:49.221
My hobbies?

00:47:51.139 --> 00:47:52.307
Going on dates?

00:47:56.561 --> 00:47:57.646
Ji-yeon!

00:47:59.272 --> 00:48:00.357
Yes?

00:48:01.066 --> 00:48:02.734
I didn't get to give you my card.

00:48:07.948 --> 00:48:08.782
Thank you.

00:48:11.493 --> 00:48:12.619
Have a safe trip home.

00:48:12.703 --> 00:48:14.079
-Goodbye.
-Right.

00:48:20.252 --> 00:48:22.004
Didn't see the step there.

00:48:22.879 --> 00:48:24.047
I'm okay.

00:48:25.007 --> 00:48:26.258
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

00:48:30.554 --> 00:48:32.347
I do look pretty good today.

00:48:40.355 --> 00:48:41.773
What's your name?

00:48:41.857 --> 00:48:43.358
-Hwang Ji-eun.
-Have you arrived?

00:48:43.859 --> 00:48:44.693
Right this way.

00:48:44.776 --> 00:48:46.778
Did you park on the ground floor?

00:48:49.114 --> 00:48:50.157
Just a second!

00:48:50.657 --> 00:48:51.867
Where should I put this?

00:48:51.950 --> 00:48:53.535
-Put it there, please.
-Sure.

00:48:56.872 --> 00:48:58.874
Family members can sit here.

00:48:58.957 --> 00:49:02.127
The awardees have designated seats,
so please sit in the front.

00:49:02.210 --> 00:49:04.046
Seo Mi-rae, come over here.

00:49:04.963 --> 00:49:07.799
Say hello.
The winner of the Best Romantasy Award.

00:49:07.883 --> 00:49:10.302
Oh, hello. I loved reading your webtoon.

00:49:10.385 --> 00:49:11.636
Thank you.

00:49:11.720 --> 00:49:14.639
Producer Seo here
will be managing you from now on.

00:49:14.723 --> 00:49:18.810
You know, Yun Song's career took off
because she met this one.

00:49:19.394 --> 00:49:21.938
-Glad to be working with you.
-The feeling's mutual.

00:49:22.022 --> 00:49:23.273
I'll leave you two to talk.

00:49:23.356 --> 00:49:24.733
-Come back later.
-Okay.

00:49:39.206 --> 00:49:40.373
It's so hectic.

00:49:40.457 --> 00:49:42.334
Did you say hello to the author?

00:49:42.417 --> 00:49:45.796
Yes. I read her work so many times
that she didn't feel like a stranger.

00:49:46.379 --> 00:49:47.672
I'm proud of myself too.

00:49:49.674 --> 00:49:52.594
It'd be nice to judge together again
next year, right?

00:49:53.595 --> 00:49:55.222
We might have a fight every day.

00:49:57.974 --> 00:49:59.142
Put those scary eyes away.

00:50:00.602 --> 00:50:02.270
Hey, what if someone walks in on us?

00:50:02.354 --> 00:50:04.648
Wait. This is it.

00:50:05.273 --> 00:50:07.067
-The storage room situation.
-Huh?

00:50:07.859 --> 00:50:11.279
There's always this kind of scene
in every office romance series.

00:50:11.780 --> 00:50:12.948
In the storage room,

00:50:13.532 --> 00:50:14.616
just the two of us.

00:50:17.244 --> 00:50:20.163
-Stop messing with me.
-Do you hate getting caught that much?

00:50:22.541 --> 00:50:24.376
Just not at work.

00:50:24.960 --> 00:50:25.794
Why?

00:50:26.628 --> 00:50:27.712
Do I embarrass you?

00:50:30.090 --> 00:50:31.675
Kyeong-nam, are the picket signs…

00:50:40.392 --> 00:50:42.185
Kyeong-nam! Are you okay?

00:50:42.269 --> 00:50:44.729
I knew it. Something felt off.

00:50:45.689 --> 00:50:48.316
I should've known
my love life wouldn't end happily.

00:50:48.400 --> 00:50:49.568
-Is he badly hurt?
-Here!

00:50:51.153 --> 00:50:52.821
-Dong-min, go with him.
-Careful.

00:50:52.904 --> 00:50:54.781
-Take care.
-I'll go with him.

00:50:57.200 --> 00:50:59.703
What was that?
I mean, how did this happen?

00:50:59.786 --> 00:51:01.621
What landed on him exactly?

00:51:02.205 --> 00:51:03.582
-Mi-rae.
-Ms. Seo!

00:51:03.665 --> 00:51:04.708
Mi-rae!

00:51:18.638 --> 00:51:19.472
Hey, you there.

00:51:20.140 --> 00:51:22.225
Get out of the way. Move aside.

00:51:22.726 --> 00:51:24.561
Why are you getting in the way?

00:51:24.644 --> 00:51:25.937
Come on, move!

00:51:26.021 --> 00:51:27.606
Unbelievable. Sheesh.

00:51:32.277 --> 00:51:33.278
Seo Mi-rae?

00:51:34.029 --> 00:51:35.113
What's wrong?

00:51:47.542 --> 00:51:50.128
Are you okay? It hurts a lot, doesn't it?

00:51:50.837 --> 00:51:52.214
What's going on with you two?

00:51:56.009 --> 00:51:56.843
What the hell?

00:51:57.552 --> 00:51:58.386
No way!

00:52:00.680 --> 00:52:03.099
If this is what I think it is,

00:52:03.183 --> 00:52:04.768
I should probably leave, huh?

00:52:05.560 --> 00:52:06.895
Are you okay?

00:52:08.021 --> 00:52:09.648
Well…

00:52:10.690 --> 00:52:11.524
Okay. I'll go.

00:52:11.608 --> 00:52:13.360
-Thank you.
-Yeah, sure.

00:52:13.944 --> 00:52:16.529
I'll keep it secret.
But you have to tell me all about it.

00:52:16.613 --> 00:52:19.032
You have to, okay? You have to!

00:52:19.824 --> 00:52:20.825
Does it hurt a lot?

00:52:22.744 --> 00:52:23.578
I'm fine.

00:52:32.379 --> 00:52:34.714
Why did you come?
You should have stayed there.

00:52:35.757 --> 00:52:37.092
You got hurt because of me.

00:52:37.717 --> 00:52:38.969
It was just an accident.

00:52:39.678 --> 00:52:40.512
No.

00:52:44.307 --> 00:52:45.892
I pushed you.

00:52:47.227 --> 00:52:51.564
I thought something bad might happen
if people were to find out about us.

00:52:53.024 --> 00:52:54.609
I did it because I was scared.

00:52:55.277 --> 00:52:56.361
I'm sorry.

00:52:57.904 --> 00:52:58.738
And

00:52:59.739 --> 00:53:01.825
there's something else I didn't tell you.

00:53:03.660 --> 00:53:05.996
After you found out
about Boyfriend on Demand,

00:53:07.497 --> 00:53:10.000
I went back to Gu Yeong-il.

00:53:13.670 --> 00:53:14.504
Why?

00:53:15.380 --> 00:53:18.550
At first, I wanted to hear
what the two of you had talked about,

00:53:19.676 --> 00:53:21.011
and after that…

00:53:23.471 --> 00:53:26.891
it was because I was scared
of how much I liked you.

00:53:29.561 --> 00:53:30.979
I thought if I liked you too much,

00:53:32.897 --> 00:53:34.566
I might struggle with it later on.

00:53:38.903 --> 00:53:41.406
Why do you keep thinking about the end?

00:53:43.783 --> 00:53:45.285
Because I'm pathetic.

00:53:48.413 --> 00:53:49.247
Right.

00:53:52.167 --> 00:53:53.960
But I'm pathetic too.

00:53:56.254 --> 00:53:58.423
When I saw Gu Yeong-il for the first time,

00:53:58.506 --> 00:54:02.218
the first thing that came to mind was,
"Did she like him before she liked me?"

00:54:02.719 --> 00:54:07.724
I wanted to grab him and ask him
about everything from start to finish,

00:54:08.266 --> 00:54:10.268
but I couldn't because of my pride.

00:54:12.812 --> 00:54:13.813
About that--

00:54:13.897 --> 00:54:15.315
But it doesn't matter anymore.

00:54:15.815 --> 00:54:18.068
I'm the one you like, after all,

00:54:18.777 --> 00:54:19.944
however it started out.

00:54:24.783 --> 00:54:26.534
I also get scared every day

00:54:27.952 --> 00:54:30.246
of how I keep falling for you
more and more.

00:54:31.956 --> 00:54:32.957
But what can I do?

00:54:35.126 --> 00:54:37.712
You ran all the way here for me
with a runny nose.

00:54:38.296 --> 00:54:39.631
How could I not like you?

00:54:52.018 --> 00:54:53.144
Easy.

00:54:53.228 --> 00:54:54.354
I'm sorry.

00:54:58.650 --> 00:55:00.026
Can't we just

00:55:01.027 --> 00:55:04.197
live in the moment and nothing else?

00:55:07.409 --> 00:55:10.662
Those who don't doubt the future
and focus on the love in front of them.

00:55:11.246 --> 00:55:12.622
That's who I draw.

00:55:20.505 --> 00:55:21.714
I'll do that.

00:55:37.105 --> 00:55:39.149
All of you,
just come with me to the States.

00:55:39.232 --> 00:55:41.192
Who am I gonna have team dinners with now?

00:55:41.276 --> 00:55:42.986
-Delicious?
-I'll miss you, sir!

00:55:43.987 --> 00:55:47.240
Oh, that's right.
I have to check this before I leave.

00:55:47.323 --> 00:55:49.993
I heard something strange recently, okay?

00:55:50.076 --> 00:55:53.413
I heard that Seo Mi-rae over there
and Park Kyeong-nam

00:55:54.247 --> 00:55:55.540
are dating.

00:56:03.965 --> 00:56:05.508
-Yes, we--
-We--

00:56:17.562 --> 00:56:19.189
That's ridiculous!

00:56:19.689 --> 00:56:22.442
See? They're not dating, you bastard.

00:56:22.525 --> 00:56:25.111
Choi Dong-min, you bastard.
You totally played me.

00:56:25.195 --> 00:56:27.572
Those two hate each other's guts, man.

00:56:27.655 --> 00:56:30.200
Hey, you guys,
let me say this one thing before I leave.

00:56:30.283 --> 00:56:32.869
Don't talk behind the authors' backs
too much.

00:56:32.952 --> 00:56:34.871
It's like shooting yourself in the foot.

00:56:34.954 --> 00:56:37.040
The authors' success is our success.

00:56:37.123 --> 00:56:39.751
-Over there!
-Let me drop some words of wisdom.

00:56:39.834 --> 00:56:42.378
-Hi. Mind if we join you?
-Sure, you--

00:56:42.462 --> 00:56:43.296
Hello!

00:56:43.379 --> 00:56:44.380
-Hello.
-Hi.

00:56:44.464 --> 00:56:45.298
Yun Song?

00:56:45.381 --> 00:56:47.175
What? Am I not allowed here?

00:56:47.258 --> 00:56:49.719
No, it's not that. I…

00:56:50.595 --> 00:56:52.096
Just take this.

00:56:52.597 --> 00:56:55.934
What could this be? What is…

00:56:56.017 --> 00:56:58.311
Wait, could this be…

00:56:59.854 --> 00:57:01.356
Wow, Yun Song!

00:57:02.398 --> 00:57:04.400
Naemo's favorite author!

00:57:05.485 --> 00:57:07.737
-You feel me, don't you?
-Sheesh.

00:57:07.820 --> 00:57:10.365
-Don't cry. I might leave.
-Oh my God!

00:57:11.115 --> 00:57:12.033
Make room, guys.

00:57:12.116 --> 00:57:13.910
-Take a seat.
-Come over here.

00:57:13.993 --> 00:57:15.286
-Sit.
-I want to drink from this.

00:57:15.370 --> 00:57:17.455
-Set her place.
-Wow, this is authentic.

00:57:17.539 --> 00:57:19.040
-It's precious.
-Looks amazing.

00:57:19.123 --> 00:57:21.626
Don't let them touch. Be careful.

00:57:24.212 --> 00:57:25.547
-So well-made.
-Look at him.

00:57:25.630 --> 00:57:27.632
-We have to drink to this.
-Cheers!

00:57:27.715 --> 00:57:29.175
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

00:57:29.259 --> 00:57:30.426
Air cheers.

00:57:37.225 --> 00:57:39.644
Hey, it looks like
you're a better drinker now.

00:57:39.727 --> 00:57:40.645
Me?

00:57:40.728 --> 00:57:42.480
I've been working out lately.

00:57:42.564 --> 00:57:46.317
I go to the gym early in the morning
and hit the climber for 30 minutes.

00:57:46.401 --> 00:57:49.195
All that exercise
must've given me a brand-new liver.

00:57:49.279 --> 00:57:50.822
I feel invincible now.

00:57:51.322 --> 00:57:52.240
What motivated you?

00:57:52.323 --> 00:57:53.700
Whoa, hold on!

00:57:54.200 --> 00:57:56.202
-I'll pick it up.
-I didn't give up.

00:57:56.286 --> 00:57:57.912
-Why?
-What was that?

00:57:59.664 --> 00:58:00.498
Well…

00:58:01.541 --> 00:58:03.459
Here. Use a new one.

00:58:03.960 --> 00:58:05.295
Okay. Thank you.

00:58:09.799 --> 00:58:12.135
May our longing

00:58:12.719 --> 00:58:15.972
One day bring us together

00:58:16.472 --> 00:58:19.058
Mr. Hwang!

00:58:19.142 --> 00:58:20.768
-Don't go!
-What are you doing?

00:58:20.852 --> 00:58:22.687
-We can't live without you.
-Wait!

00:58:22.770 --> 00:58:24.647
I'll be back later this year.

00:58:24.731 --> 00:58:27.191
So don't ignore my calls,
or you'll pay the price.

00:58:27.275 --> 00:58:30.111
-Really? You'll be coming back?
-Of course. I'll be back.

00:58:30.194 --> 00:58:31.988
-Don't forget about us!
-I won't!

00:58:32.071 --> 00:58:34.782
-Have a safe trip.
-And take care of your health.

00:58:34.866 --> 00:58:36.117
I'm gonna miss you.

00:58:36.200 --> 00:58:38.870
Try to cut down on the coffee
while you're at it.

00:58:38.953 --> 00:58:40.288
God, Yun!

00:58:40.371 --> 00:58:43.541
Seeing how much you care about me
makes my leaving feel so real.

00:58:44.375 --> 00:58:46.210
How much is this thing anyway?

00:58:47.629 --> 00:58:49.339
Hey, let's have a drink!

00:58:51.132 --> 00:58:52.717
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

00:58:52.800 --> 00:58:54.135
-Love you!
-Love you all!

00:58:54.218 --> 00:58:56.512
Hey, the company card's been unleashed!

00:59:10.902 --> 00:59:15.239
Maybe goodbyes aren't as bad as we think.

00:59:49.190 --> 00:59:50.358
It's been a while.

00:59:56.406 --> 00:59:57.448
It has.

00:59:59.158 --> 01:00:01.661
If it took you this long to come find me,

01:00:01.744 --> 01:00:04.664
it must've gone really well
or really badly, huh?

01:00:06.624 --> 01:00:07.458
Did it go badly?

01:00:12.797 --> 01:00:14.132
Man, that's a shame.

01:00:18.720 --> 01:00:19.887
Are you gonna be okay?

01:00:21.139 --> 01:00:24.308
You might end up lonelier and more anxious
than when you were alone.

01:00:25.268 --> 01:00:28.104
And neither one of your feelings
will stay the same forever.

01:00:30.565 --> 01:00:31.816
That just might be.

01:00:32.900 --> 01:00:34.026
You're okay with that?

01:00:36.529 --> 01:00:37.363
I am.

01:00:38.614 --> 01:00:39.532
Why's that?

01:00:40.867 --> 01:00:42.535
That's just how people are.

01:00:42.618 --> 01:00:44.704
We choose to set out on adventures,

01:00:45.455 --> 01:00:47.123
despite knowing the dangers.

01:00:58.968 --> 01:01:01.053
Hop on. It's dangerous here at night.

01:01:02.722 --> 01:01:03.931
You know I won't get on.

01:01:07.185 --> 01:01:10.188
Take care. Thanks for everything.

01:01:12.190 --> 01:01:13.733
Are you really going to end this?

01:01:18.237 --> 01:01:22.492
Ms. Seo Mi-rae, would you like
to part ways with Gu Yeong-il?

01:01:28.998 --> 01:01:31.083
You'll manage fine, right?
Your relationship.

01:01:33.628 --> 01:01:36.798
Just follow your heart.
Be brave even when you're afraid.

01:01:38.549 --> 01:01:39.634
I know that too.

01:01:41.302 --> 01:01:43.095
I remember when you were clueless.

01:01:45.890 --> 01:01:46.891
Bye now.

01:02:07.745 --> 01:02:10.248
YES

01:02:15.169 --> 01:02:16.003
Kyeong-nam!

01:02:18.923 --> 01:02:20.633
You're running again. I told you not to.

01:02:23.219 --> 01:02:24.053
It's dangerous.

01:02:24.136 --> 01:02:26.347
Relationships are dangerous.

01:02:29.600 --> 01:02:31.727
Love is even more dangerous.

01:02:36.357 --> 01:02:38.693
If you head out earlier,
you won't have to run.

01:02:39.527 --> 01:02:40.862
You and your nagging.

01:02:52.999 --> 01:02:56.002
But this time, I think I'll be okay.

01:02:57.461 --> 01:02:58.546
Because it's us.

01:06:07.985 --> 01:06:12.990
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon